♪ Take flight
as the world turns ♪

01:36.357 --> 01:38.272
♪ Keep the colors in the lines

01:38.315 --> 01:40.926
♪ Take flight

01:40.970 --> 01:42.841
♪ Dreams never die

01:42.885 --> 01:48.282
♪♪

01:48.325 --> 01:52.286
♪ Keep the colors
in the lines ♪

01:52.329 --> 01:54.244
♪ Keep the colors
in the lines ♪

01:54.288 --> 01:57.204
♪ Take flight

01:57.247 --> 01:59.728
It's 7:00,
probably.

02:02.252 --> 02:04.689
Auntie,
should I call my mom?

02:04.733 --> 02:06.735
She's probably awake in L.A.
by now.

02:06.778 --> 02:07.953
Mnh-mnh.

02:07.997 --> 02:10.260
Ain't no use
in telling your mother.

02:10.304 --> 02:15.178
She got that big meeting
with all those bigwigs.

02:15.222 --> 02:17.180
No, just let her
focus on that.

02:17.224 --> 02:18.573
Alright.

02:18.616 --> 02:21.793
Woman on PA:
Dr. Jones, report to admitting.

02:21.837 --> 02:23.534
Violet.

02:23.578 --> 02:25.667
Ralph Angel,
Hollywood.

02:25.710 --> 02:28.974
Mm, t-t-thank you for coming
as soon as you could.

02:29.018 --> 02:31.151
Respectfully, Violet,
please don't thank me like

02:31.194 --> 02:32.717
I'm a stranger
doing you a favor.

02:32.761 --> 02:34.763
He's my father, and I don't
have to be thanked

02:34.806 --> 02:35.981
to come and see him.

02:36.025 --> 02:38.593
You're right.
That was insensitive of me.

02:38.636 --> 02:39.811
I'm sorry.

02:39.855 --> 02:41.378
Why was he down there
in the first place?

02:41.422 --> 02:45.252
I mean, working a vaccine drive
at his age?

02:45.295 --> 02:46.601
I mean,
he's not a doctor.

02:46.644 --> 02:48.255
And none of this
is anyone's fault, Billie.

02:48.298 --> 02:50.474
If you want to blame
someone, blame me.

02:50.518 --> 02:52.607
It was my event,
and Prosper was happy

02:52.650 --> 02:54.478
to be there
for his community.

02:54.522 --> 02:56.741
Dr. Jones, you are needed --

02:56.785 --> 02:58.830
I'm Billie Denton,
Prosper's daughter.

02:58.874 --> 03:00.310
Now, I don't know
what you've been told,

03:00.354 --> 03:02.399
but I'm the only
blood relative here

03:02.443 --> 03:03.661
and should be
the only one to receive

03:03.705 --> 03:05.272
medical information
about him.

03:05.315 --> 03:06.708
Now, this is
his power of attorney

03:06.751 --> 03:09.014
and other medical forms,
which are all up to date,

03:09.058 --> 03:11.016
and I can share them
with the appropriate clerks.

03:11.060 --> 03:15.282
We also have supplemental and
catastrophic insurance for him.

03:15.325 --> 03:16.500
I want you to know this,
Doctor,

03:16.544 --> 03:18.502
because I don't want you
to hold back

03:18.546 --> 03:20.678
on anything
that'll make him better.

03:20.722 --> 03:22.071
I want to make sure
that he is getting

03:22.114 --> 03:24.204
the best specialized care.

03:24.247 --> 03:25.944
Of course.
Um, come with me,

03:25.988 --> 03:29.296
and I'll be sure that
you're brought up to speed.

03:29.339 --> 03:31.950
Um, we'll need to get you
swabbed first.

03:33.604 --> 03:36.346
[ Woman on PA speaking
indistinctly ]

03:36.390 --> 03:38.348
Go home
and get some rest.

03:38.392 --> 03:40.742
I'll stay here
and look after Prosper.

03:40.785 --> 03:44.224
Hollywood has a TV interview
for "The Real Spot" later,

03:44.267 --> 03:46.356
and y'all have been here
all night.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.358
Alright, baby,
I'll call you in a bit.

03:48.402 --> 03:49.794
See y'all a little later,
alright?

03:49.838 --> 03:52.493
Alright.

03:52.536 --> 03:55.539
I need to, um,
drop a prescription off

03:55.583 --> 03:57.367
at the pharmacy
before we leave.

03:57.411 --> 04:01.023
Meet me out front.

04:01.066 --> 04:03.939
Darla,
I'll walk you out.

04:03.982 --> 04:05.680
Later, Unc.
-Later.

04:09.553 --> 04:11.294
Where you headed?

04:11.338 --> 04:13.601
OB appointment today.

04:13.644 --> 04:16.473
About 25 minutes out.

04:16.517 --> 04:18.519
Find out if it's
a little boy or girl.

04:18.562 --> 04:19.998
That's wonderful, Ra.

04:20.042 --> 04:23.567
You always got to have something
good to look forward to.

04:23.611 --> 04:26.091
Hold on to the good,
right?

04:26.135 --> 04:27.441
Love you.

04:27.484 --> 04:28.920
Love you more.

04:28.964 --> 04:30.922
Be safe out here.

04:30.966 --> 04:32.315
Okay.
You, too.

04:32.359 --> 04:37.755
♪♪

04:37.799 --> 04:42.804
♪♪

04:42.847 --> 04:46.373
Bro, then come
to the study group.

04:46.416 --> 04:47.722
That's what it's for, man.

04:47.765 --> 04:49.332
You're not retaining
the information.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.291
-Hey, watch it.
-You could just join a --

04:51.334 --> 04:52.770
-Back off me, man.
-Step over here.

04:52.814 --> 04:54.206
Prosper: Look, I'm sick
and tired of this crap,

04:54.250 --> 04:55.730
so don't put your hands on me,
you understand?

04:55.773 --> 04:56.861
-You need to relax.
-Don't tell me to relax.

04:56.905 --> 04:58.776
-That's it. That's it.
-Hey!

04:58.820 --> 05:01.431
-Micah.
-Roll down the window.

05:01.475 --> 05:03.955
-Micah.
-Get out of the car!

05:03.999 --> 05:05.870
Micah!

05:05.914 --> 05:07.611
Man, you alright?

05:10.658 --> 05:13.443
Yeah, I'm just...

05:13.487 --> 05:16.011
Man,
this whole thing is crazy.

05:16.054 --> 05:18.579
We were just trying to do
something good, you know?

05:18.622 --> 05:20.058
Hey, look here, man,
why don't you come by

05:20.102 --> 05:21.451
The Real Spot tomorrow?

05:21.495 --> 05:23.061
We got a television crew
doing a spot

05:23.105 --> 05:24.628
about the grand opening.

05:24.672 --> 05:25.847
Can show you that wall.

05:25.890 --> 05:27.936
You can put your pictures
up there.

05:27.979 --> 05:29.459
Yeah.

05:29.503 --> 05:31.069
Yeah,
that could be cool.

05:31.113 --> 05:32.897
I'll come by.

05:32.941 --> 05:35.204
Alright, man.

05:35.247 --> 05:36.945
See you tomorrow.

05:41.123 --> 05:44.518
The January 6th insurrection
showed us now more than ever

05:44.561 --> 05:45.997
that we've got to nurture
and amplify

05:46.041 --> 05:48.826
strong local political leaders
at the state level

05:48.870 --> 05:51.002
and possibly
the national stage.

05:51.046 --> 05:54.092
We've had our eye on you
for a minute, Charley.

05:54.136 --> 05:55.790
Well, thank you.

05:55.833 --> 05:59.837
But there's still a lot of work
that needs to be done in St. Jo.

05:59.881 --> 06:03.232
Think about what you can do
in a state level to help St. Jo.

06:03.275 --> 06:06.670
You're a charismatic, outspoken
Black woman with an MBA

06:06.714 --> 06:08.498
and an already
high profile.

06:08.542 --> 06:10.935
Exactly who we're looking to
as the future.

06:10.979 --> 06:13.068
The party is looking to take
back state legislatures

06:13.111 --> 06:15.549
across the country,
and we feel you could make

06:15.592 --> 06:18.465
an excellent candidate
for state senator.

06:18.508 --> 06:20.815
Mind if we spread
your name around?

06:21.424 --> 06:23.687
[ Chuckles ]

06:23.731 --> 06:26.734
That would be
wonderful.

06:26.777 --> 06:29.824
But if we take this conversation
further,

06:29.867 --> 06:34.655
you understand I'll need to
take some time to consider.

06:34.698 --> 06:36.831
As long as you don't
take too long.

06:36.874 --> 06:38.528
The one thing the pandemic
has shown me

06:38.572 --> 06:41.792
is that
nothing's promised.

06:41.836 --> 06:44.229
Don't let a great opportunity
pass you by.

06:44.273 --> 06:45.970
One last thing.

06:46.014 --> 06:49.670
There will be a lot of scrutiny
on you if you move forward.

06:49.713 --> 06:51.280
If there are issues
or sensitivities

06:51.323 --> 06:53.543
we should know about to lend
our full-fledged support,

06:53.587 --> 06:56.503
you need to disclose them now,
up front.

06:59.984 --> 07:01.421
No skeletons here.

07:01.464 --> 07:08.950
♪♪

07:10.865 --> 07:16.479
[ Woman on PA speaking
indistinctly ]

07:16.523 --> 07:18.263
Is it alright
if I sit here?

07:18.307 --> 07:20.527
Of course it is,
Violet.

07:20.570 --> 07:22.093
Is a doctor in there?

07:22.137 --> 07:24.052
Yes.

07:24.095 --> 07:27.577
He told me about the planned
treatment to induce a coma.

07:27.621 --> 07:29.187
Said
you signed off on it.

07:29.231 --> 07:30.580
I tried to reach you.

07:30.624 --> 07:31.929
I was on a plane.

07:31.973 --> 07:33.496
I know.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.498
So I did what I thought
was right.

07:35.542 --> 07:37.282
It was the doctor's
recommendation.

07:37.326 --> 07:38.458
I won't apologize
for it.

07:38.501 --> 07:41.417
I am not asking you
to apologize.

07:41.461 --> 07:45.769
Look, I really appreciate you
helping my father.

07:45.813 --> 07:47.858
Okay?
But I'm here now, so --

07:47.902 --> 07:49.556
How is he?
-How is he?

07:49.599 --> 07:52.689
Honestly, I'm not seeing
as much improvement

07:52.733 --> 07:54.952
as I had hoped for
by now.

07:54.996 --> 07:57.999
I'd like to try a therapeutic
hypothermia treatment.

07:58.042 --> 07:59.261
Hypothermia?

07:59.304 --> 08:00.610
It's perfectly safe.

08:00.654 --> 08:02.612
It's a controlled lowering
of the body temperature

08:02.656 --> 08:04.875
to around 35 degrees.

08:04.919 --> 08:07.878
It may reduce the inflammation
on the brain.

08:07.922 --> 08:08.923
It may?

08:08.966 --> 08:11.316
You don't sound
very certain.

08:11.360 --> 08:12.970
I can't give
any guarantees.

08:13.014 --> 08:15.799
Everybody's body reacts
differently.

08:15.843 --> 08:19.586
My recommendation is that
you consider it.

08:19.629 --> 08:21.109
Excuse me.

08:27.855 --> 08:32.468
Well, I-I suggest that you don't
shut this down too quick.

08:32.512 --> 08:36.864
This isn't a state-of-the-art
medical facility, Violet.

08:36.907 --> 08:38.909
I know Prosper,
and he would want --

08:38.953 --> 08:41.085
This isn't about
what he wants.

08:41.129 --> 08:42.652
We leave it to him
and he'd say,

08:42.696 --> 08:46.090
"Just take me home
and let me sleep it off."

08:46.134 --> 08:48.440
This is about
what will save him.

08:48.484 --> 08:50.617
[ Scoffs ]

08:56.579 --> 08:59.364
You are not alone.

08:59.408 --> 09:01.584
That man...

09:01.628 --> 09:06.589
has been my friend
for 35 years.

09:06.633 --> 09:08.548
Now, there are some decisions
to make,

09:08.591 --> 09:11.202
and we can
make them together.

09:11.246 --> 09:13.161
I should have insisted
that he move with me

09:13.204 --> 09:14.858
to Chicago years ago.

09:14.902 --> 09:17.078
'Cause this never
would've happened.

09:17.121 --> 09:19.863
But he insisted
that he was fine

09:19.907 --> 09:22.431
and that if he ever
did need anything then

09:22.474 --> 09:24.302
"the Bordelons are here,
Peach.

09:24.346 --> 09:26.087
They'll look after me."

09:26.130 --> 09:29.046
Well, look at him now.

09:29.090 --> 09:31.179
He couldn't have been
more wrong.

09:33.094 --> 09:37.794
You got a lot of bad judgment
in you, Miss Thing.

09:37.838 --> 09:41.668
The last time Prosper
was here in the hospital,

09:41.711 --> 09:44.279
you couldn't be bothered
to come see him.

09:47.021 --> 09:51.460
You don't care for my father
more than I do, Violet.

09:51.503 --> 09:53.201
He could die.

09:53.244 --> 09:56.683
And I don't have the energy to
deal with you or any of this.

09:56.726 --> 09:58.598
Doctor!

10:03.298 --> 10:05.082
As Prosper Denton's
next of kin,

10:05.126 --> 10:06.736
I want Violet Bordelon
removed

10:06.780 --> 10:09.043
from the list
of approved visitors.

10:09.086 --> 10:10.610
What?

10:10.653 --> 10:12.002
Oh, no,
you cannot do that.

10:12.046 --> 10:14.657
In fact, I don't want
any of the Bordelons

10:14.701 --> 10:17.878
anywhere near his room.

10:17.921 --> 10:20.881
Dr. Holland,
now, you know me.

10:20.924 --> 10:24.014
I'm the one that was here
every day

10:24.058 --> 10:27.148
the last time
he was here.

10:27.191 --> 10:29.280
I'm sorry.

10:29.324 --> 10:31.587
I have to abide
by the family's wishes.

10:31.631 --> 10:36.636
♪♪

10:42.685 --> 10:45.819
♪♪

10:54.784 --> 10:55.785
Hey.

10:58.179 --> 10:59.528
Micah?

11:02.705 --> 11:03.967
Micah?

11:04.011 --> 11:05.490
-Back off me, man.
-Step over here.

11:05.534 --> 11:07.231
Prosper: Look, I'm sick
and tired of this crap,

11:07.275 --> 11:08.580
so don't put your hands on me,
you understand?

11:08.624 --> 11:10.234
-You need to relax.
-Don't tell me to relax.

11:10.278 --> 11:12.672
-That's it. That's it.
-Hey!

11:12.715 --> 11:14.804
Isaiah: Hey.

11:14.848 --> 11:17.067
You with us, man?

11:17.111 --> 11:18.982
Yeah, man.
I just...

11:19.026 --> 11:21.289
didn't get a lot of sleep
last night.

11:21.332 --> 11:23.334
W-What were you saying?

11:23.378 --> 11:24.988
I was just asking about
the vaccine drive.

11:25.032 --> 11:27.643
You know, I heard that police
came in, they were siding

11:27.687 --> 11:30.820
with the very folks who caused
the issue in the first place.

11:30.864 --> 11:32.953
Man,
you know how they do.

11:32.996 --> 11:34.519
They do what they want.

11:34.563 --> 11:36.739
When they want,
how they want.

11:38.959 --> 11:42.266
It happened to me.

11:42.310 --> 11:45.443
Yeah, happened to me.

11:45.487 --> 11:47.445
I'm sorry, man.
I didn't know.

11:49.709 --> 11:51.014
When did it go down?

11:51.058 --> 11:52.755
Few years back.

11:56.150 --> 11:58.761
But it stays with you.

11:58.805 --> 12:01.068
Longer than you'd think
it would.

12:01.111 --> 12:03.766
And I'm sure
2020 didn't help.

12:07.422 --> 12:11.252
Our survival is a miracle,
you know?

12:11.295 --> 12:14.777
You're right.

12:14.821 --> 12:18.215
If you ever want to talk,
man...

12:18.259 --> 12:21.001
you got brothers around,
okay?

12:21.044 --> 12:23.612
Yeah, man.
Thanks.

12:23.655 --> 12:26.528
Yeah.

12:26.571 --> 12:29.487
Catch you later, okay?Alright, peace.

12:39.454 --> 12:41.064
Charley:
Micah? What's up?

12:41.108 --> 12:43.327
Hey, I'm just, uh...

12:43.371 --> 12:45.068
calling you to see
how everything went.

12:45.112 --> 12:46.853
How was the meeting?

12:46.896 --> 12:49.812
Everything went fine.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.727
You didn't just call to ask
about my meeting.

12:51.771 --> 12:55.078
I can hear it
in your voice.

12:55.122 --> 12:57.167
Um...

12:57.211 --> 12:59.909
Did Aunt Vi call you?

12:59.953 --> 13:02.390
No.

13:02.433 --> 13:05.741
Micah,
what's going on?

13:05.785 --> 13:08.309
Look, I don't want you to panic,
but, um...

13:10.311 --> 13:13.705
Mr. Prosper...

13:13.749 --> 13:15.446
he -- he was beaten.

13:15.490 --> 13:17.448
Oh, my God.
He's in a coma.

13:17.492 --> 13:23.237
What?
I -- I -- I'll, uh -- I'll --

13:23.280 --> 13:25.326
I'll head home
f-first thing.

13:25.369 --> 13:28.111
No, see, Aunt Vi didn't want
to ruin your trip.

13:28.155 --> 13:30.679
I just wanted to call you
and tell you to stay there,

13:30.722 --> 13:33.334
and I'll keep you updated
on everything, okay?

13:33.377 --> 13:35.075
I'll be home
on the next flight.

13:35.118 --> 13:43.170
♪♪

13:43.213 --> 13:51.265
♪♪

13:51.308 --> 13:53.180
[ Cellphone rings ]

13:53.223 --> 13:54.834
Aunt Vi,
what's going on?

13:54.877 --> 13:56.487
Ooh, that Billie.

13:56.531 --> 13:58.881
Barreling in here like
a bull in a china shop,

13:58.925 --> 14:01.362
trying to take over.

14:01.405 --> 14:03.233
Aunt Vi,
can you hear me?

14:03.277 --> 14:04.931
Yes, baby,
I can hear you.

14:04.974 --> 14:06.193
What did she do?

14:06.236 --> 14:07.890
She says that
I can't visit Prosper --

14:07.934 --> 14:10.588
not at the hospital
or at the house.

14:10.632 --> 14:13.069
None of us can.
We've been banned.

14:13.113 --> 14:15.550
What? Why?

14:15.593 --> 14:17.508
I know that y'all
used to be friends.

14:17.552 --> 14:20.163
I suggest that you talk
some sense into her

14:20.207 --> 14:23.166
before we have
a real problem.

14:23.210 --> 14:25.168
I'll --
I'll talk to Billie.

14:25.212 --> 14:26.822
Work this out.

14:26.866 --> 14:28.868
Good.
You do that.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.395
[ Sighs ]

14:34.438 --> 14:36.136
Hey, Billie, it's Nova.

14:36.179 --> 14:37.398
Please call me.

14:37.441 --> 14:40.401
It's about Prosper and Aunt Vi.

14:40.444 --> 14:42.490
I look forward
to talking with you.

14:44.318 --> 14:45.972
Thanks.

14:46.015 --> 14:47.147
[ Sighs ]

14:47.190 --> 14:48.931
[ Cellphone chimes ]

14:53.718 --> 14:55.459
Nova: Hi.
Yes, can I get a sheriff

14:55.503 --> 14:57.070
down to my vaccine drive?

14:57.113 --> 14:59.333
[ Scoffs ]

15:02.423 --> 15:03.554
[ Line rings ]

15:03.598 --> 15:05.295
Liza: Nova,
I was about to call you.

15:05.339 --> 15:07.471
You're trending.Yeah, I saw.

15:07.515 --> 15:08.864
Can you schedule
a staff meeting?

15:08.908 --> 15:10.387
We need to nip this
in the --

15:10.431 --> 15:13.042
[ Static ]Hello? Hello?

15:13.086 --> 15:14.696
Liza, did you hear that?You're breaking up.

15:14.739 --> 15:16.872
Hello? Hello?
Liza,

15:16.916 --> 15:20.049
I don't feel comfortable
talking on this line.

15:20.093 --> 15:23.183
Can you just set up a meeting
and e-mail me the info?

15:23.226 --> 15:30.973
♪♪

15:31.017 --> 15:34.237
So, I suppose you're ready
for the big news.

15:34.281 --> 15:36.544
Lay it on us.

15:36.587 --> 15:38.459
You are having...

15:38.502 --> 15:39.460
a little girl.

15:39.503 --> 15:42.506
Mm!
Really?

15:42.550 --> 15:46.075
Look at us raising us
a little baby girl, huh?

15:46.119 --> 15:47.468
Oh, my goodness.

15:47.511 --> 15:49.078
Can we get a printout?

15:49.122 --> 15:51.428
Of course.

15:51.472 --> 15:54.475
What's up, Princess?

15:54.518 --> 15:55.519
Proud of you.

15:55.563 --> 15:58.000
Proud of you.

15:59.828 --> 16:01.134
Ah.

16:01.177 --> 16:02.135
There you go.

16:02.178 --> 16:04.137
Thank you.

16:04.180 --> 16:05.268
Oh, my God.

16:05.312 --> 16:07.314
Look how beautiful
she is.

16:07.357 --> 16:10.230
Look at her little stomach
and her head.

16:10.273 --> 16:11.622
Her little feet.

16:11.666 --> 16:13.973
Look like she got your head.She has your head.

16:14.016 --> 16:14.930
That's gigantic.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.366
No, that's you.
That's you.

16:16.410 --> 16:18.107
Her little belly.

16:18.151 --> 16:20.153
Shoot,
that's us, huh?

16:20.196 --> 16:21.937
What's up, baby girl?

16:23.983 --> 16:24.984
Baby girl.

16:33.601 --> 16:36.038
What you got
in that bag?

16:36.082 --> 16:39.259
Just a little care package for
the shelter over at St. Agnes.

16:39.302 --> 16:40.521
What'd they say?

16:40.564 --> 16:42.653
It's confirmed, baby.

16:42.697 --> 16:46.048
St. Jo's News is coming to
The Real Spot at 5:00

16:46.092 --> 16:49.269
to do a segment on it.

16:49.312 --> 16:50.792
That is wonderful,
baby.

16:50.835 --> 16:53.490
Yeah, they say that
it's gonna go perfect with

16:53.534 --> 16:57.233
their "Comeback after COVID"
series, yeah.

16:57.277 --> 16:58.800
I don't know, baby.
I'm...

16:58.843 --> 17:01.324
sort of thinking
about canceling it.

17:01.368 --> 17:04.066
Cancel?
Why?

17:04.110 --> 17:06.982
All this stuff that's
going on with Prosper.

17:07.026 --> 17:10.420
Just don't seem right doing
this PR thing right now.

17:10.464 --> 17:13.684
This PR thing is gonna generate
excitement for your launch.

17:13.728 --> 17:16.992
You've been working on
this opening for over a year.

17:17.036 --> 17:20.474
You need everything
to make it a success.

17:20.517 --> 17:22.563
He would want that,
Hollywood.

17:22.606 --> 17:24.304
You think so?

17:24.347 --> 17:25.740
I know so.

17:25.783 --> 17:27.350
The rest of us,
we got Prosper.

17:27.394 --> 17:30.527
Baby, they ain't even letting
you go see Prosper right now.

17:30.571 --> 17:32.051
Do you think that
I'm gonna let

17:32.094 --> 17:35.097
Prosper's fast-tailed girl
keep me from my friend?

17:35.141 --> 17:38.448
Shoot. The day that happens is
the day I'll hang it all up.

17:38.492 --> 17:39.623
Best believe that.

17:39.667 --> 17:42.191
I hear you, baby.

17:42.235 --> 17:44.106
Now I need you
to get there early, okay?

17:44.150 --> 17:45.586
I need my good-luck charm.

17:45.629 --> 17:48.850
I am gonna be there,

17:48.893 --> 17:51.896
and we both gonna be
camera-ready.

17:51.940 --> 17:53.463
Shoot.

17:53.507 --> 17:57.554
St. Jo viewers don't know
what they about to get hit with,

17:57.598 --> 18:03.865
all this sexy chocolate
up in they TVs.

18:03.908 --> 18:07.608
Say more, Boo.
Go ahead, get ready, alright?

18:10.437 --> 18:13.048
[ Chuckles ]
I told Prosper

18:13.092 --> 18:16.182
I'd show him the sonogram
once we got it.

18:16.225 --> 18:20.447
You should take it to him
when he gets out.

18:20.490 --> 18:23.102
So you're just not gonna share,
huh?

18:23.145 --> 18:24.712
Look at you.

18:24.755 --> 18:26.583
I'm sorry,
Ralph Angel.

18:26.627 --> 18:28.281
That is kind of rude.
Have one.

18:28.324 --> 18:30.631
I'm good.

18:30.674 --> 18:32.285
Thank you, though.
Okay.

18:32.328 --> 18:35.766
I will admit my cravings have
been a little out of control.

18:35.810 --> 18:38.073
This is, like, my second box
this week.

18:38.117 --> 18:40.249
That's your third.

18:40.293 --> 18:41.250
Don't.

18:41.294 --> 18:42.947
Do not count
my beignets.

18:42.991 --> 18:44.732
My beignets
are my business.

18:44.775 --> 18:46.516
I'm just saying.

18:46.560 --> 18:48.127
Okay, that is it.

18:48.170 --> 18:49.737
From this moment on,

18:49.780 --> 18:51.956
it's gonna be yoga,
green shakes,

18:52.000 --> 18:54.568
and I'm gonna get
one of those speakers

18:54.611 --> 18:58.137
you stick up your, um, hoo-hah
that plays classical music.

18:58.180 --> 19:00.661
They do not make that.

19:00.704 --> 19:04.099
I'm gonna do everything
right this time.

19:04.143 --> 19:08.538
Actually, when we were
at the hospital yesterday,

19:08.582 --> 19:12.107
it was understaffed
and falling apart.

19:14.501 --> 19:15.980
Yeah, Nova said
all the hospitals

19:16.024 --> 19:19.288
have been messed up
with COVID.

19:19.332 --> 19:21.769
So...

19:21.812 --> 19:25.120
what do you think about...

19:25.164 --> 19:27.427
a home birth?

19:27.470 --> 19:28.993
Home birth?

19:29.037 --> 19:31.822
Look.
I've been doing some research,

19:31.866 --> 19:33.346
and as long as I'm healthy

19:33.389 --> 19:37.001
and it's not a high-risk
pregnancy, it's very safe.

19:37.045 --> 19:38.481
Look.

19:38.525 --> 19:40.744
Home births have lower rates
of post-partum hemorrhage

19:40.788 --> 19:43.573
or lacerations and fewer
surgical interventions,

19:43.617 --> 19:45.445
especially for
Black women.

19:45.488 --> 19:46.576
Okay.

19:46.620 --> 19:48.839
But what about
the downsides?

19:48.883 --> 19:51.842
I mean, people give birth
at a hospital for a reason.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.583
It's 'cause it's safer.

19:53.627 --> 19:56.847
No pregnancy is completely safe,
Ralph Angel.

19:56.891 --> 19:59.589
You think I'll feel safer
giving birth

19:59.633 --> 20:02.375
in a hospital
that's overstretched?

20:02.418 --> 20:08.032
I want to bring our little girl
into the world on this farm,

20:08.076 --> 20:10.992
surrounded by all the things
that I love.

20:11.035 --> 20:13.037
Why don't we
hire a doula?

20:13.081 --> 20:14.213
A what?

20:14.256 --> 20:15.649
A midwife.

20:15.692 --> 20:19.696
We will follow everything
she says to the letter.

20:19.740 --> 20:22.221
We can do this.

20:22.264 --> 20:23.961
It's gonna be okay.

20:27.748 --> 20:31.360
Anything happen,
we hightail it to a hospital.

20:31.404 --> 20:33.057
Mm-hmm.
No arguments.

20:33.101 --> 20:34.450
Mnh-mnh.

20:34.494 --> 20:36.147
Okay?

20:36.191 --> 20:37.932
Okay.

20:39.238 --> 20:43.329
[ Man on PA speaking
indistinctly ]

20:43.372 --> 20:45.374
Charley?

20:45.418 --> 20:48.247
Billie.

20:48.290 --> 20:50.379
Wow.

20:50.423 --> 20:51.815
Hi.

20:51.859 --> 20:56.646
It's been, like, forever
since I've seen you or...

20:56.690 --> 20:58.866
Outside a magazine,
of course.

20:58.909 --> 21:01.956
I, uh -- I just got back
from LA, came straight here.

21:01.999 --> 21:04.393
How are you holding up,
Billie?

21:04.437 --> 21:05.960
How's Prosper doing?

21:06.003 --> 21:08.310
He's --
He's hanging in there.

21:08.354 --> 21:09.920
Yeah, I just --
I wanted to stop in

21:09.964 --> 21:11.792
and see him
for a minute.

21:11.835 --> 21:15.535
Yeah, I decided, um...

21:15.578 --> 21:16.971
we need to limit visits.

21:17.014 --> 21:18.842
I hope you understand.

21:18.886 --> 21:20.627
Listen, I don't have
anything against you.

21:20.670 --> 21:23.412
You've been
really good to me.

21:23.456 --> 21:25.240
It's just...

21:25.284 --> 21:28.330
Well, your family --
your aunt --

21:28.374 --> 21:30.854
has been really
crossing the line.

21:30.898 --> 21:33.814
And I needed to set up
some boundaries.

21:35.990 --> 21:37.731
What does that mean?

21:37.774 --> 21:39.950
I decided that, for now,

21:39.994 --> 21:43.127
it's best that
he not have visitors.

21:43.171 --> 21:44.781
I just need to maintain
a little quiet

21:44.825 --> 21:47.131
and order
in this whole situation.

21:53.355 --> 21:55.966
♪♪

21:56.010 --> 22:00.144
You know, you and I,
we're very similar.

22:00.188 --> 22:02.973
I sought order once,
too.

22:03.017 --> 22:07.151
It was really control
that I wanted.

22:07.195 --> 22:11.155
Thought I could just fit
my father into my schedule.

22:11.199 --> 22:17.858
♪♪

22:17.901 --> 22:20.164
I missed his last moments

22:20.208 --> 22:24.430
chasing something
that wasn't real.

22:24.473 --> 22:26.475
Power and money.

22:29.913 --> 22:33.352
I'll never
get that back.

22:33.395 --> 22:35.876
So...

22:35.919 --> 22:39.880
I hope
you're luckier than me.

22:39.923 --> 22:41.882
And if you are...

22:45.059 --> 22:50.107
I hope that you'll listen
to him, love him,

22:50.151 --> 22:55.069
and respect him
by letting others love him.

22:55.112 --> 22:58.551
If you don't, then...

22:58.594 --> 23:03.686
you're just trying to control
him, too -- him and us.

23:03.730 --> 23:07.995
I was never really the one
trying to control things.

23:08.038 --> 23:09.300
For me and him,
it was...

23:09.344 --> 23:13.435
it was probably
the other way around.

23:13.479 --> 23:19.441
♪♪

23:19.485 --> 23:23.010
No one knows a relationship
like the people in it.

23:25.273 --> 23:26.448
Okay.

23:26.492 --> 23:29.582
Um, I'll be around
if you need anything.

23:29.625 --> 23:31.410
Anything at all.

23:31.453 --> 23:32.889
Thank you.

23:32.933 --> 23:39.461
♪♪

23:39.505 --> 23:44.466
♪♪

23:51.647 --> 23:52.605
Ohh!

23:52.648 --> 23:54.258
Oh, hi.

23:54.302 --> 23:56.565
I'm so sorry.
I didn't meant to startle you.

23:56.609 --> 23:57.914
I'm sorry.

23:57.958 --> 24:01.048
My nerves have been
a bit frazzled lately.

24:01.091 --> 24:02.484
Dominic, right?

24:02.528 --> 24:04.878
I met Loretta when she was
moving in the other day.

24:04.921 --> 24:06.357
How are you enjoying
the new place?

24:06.401 --> 24:09.709
Uh, I -- I feel like I've barely
spent any time in there.

24:09.752 --> 24:11.058
Traveling so much.

24:11.101 --> 24:12.320
I just flew back from New York
this morning.

24:12.363 --> 24:14.104
I see you're doing
a little decorating.

24:14.148 --> 24:16.455
Oh.
No, shoot, I wish.

24:16.498 --> 24:17.760
It's actually for work.

24:17.804 --> 24:19.109
I'm putting together
a multimedia exhibit

24:19.153 --> 24:21.634
about the Black
northern migration for Tulane.

24:21.677 --> 24:22.983
Oh, my alma mater.

24:23.026 --> 24:24.027
You teach there?

24:24.071 --> 24:25.942
Yeah,
cultural anthropology.

24:25.986 --> 24:27.857
That's amazing.

24:27.901 --> 24:29.293
Hey, Loretta!

24:29.337 --> 24:30.425
Hey, Nova!

24:30.469 --> 24:32.471
Alright, well,
really good to meet you.

24:32.514 --> 24:34.473
Fan of your work,
your voice.

24:34.516 --> 24:36.518
Thank you.
And, uh, welcome.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.781
Thank you.
Alright, you have a good day.

24:38.825 --> 24:40.174
You too now.
Thank you.

24:40.217 --> 24:41.784
We're just glad to
have it back open.

24:41.828 --> 24:44.134
It's a place where the fellas
can just get around, talk.

24:44.178 --> 24:45.788
But, you know, we talk about
the real issues

24:45.832 --> 24:47.224
that are affecting us
right now.

24:47.268 --> 24:49.139
-Hollywood.
-Hey! Hey!

24:49.183 --> 24:50.445
What's up, man?

24:50.489 --> 24:52.447
Hey, so good to see
a friendly face.

24:52.491 --> 24:54.014
These nerves are getting
the best of me.

24:54.057 --> 24:55.668
Man, don't let them.
You look great.

24:55.711 --> 24:56.712
Do I?
Yeah.

24:56.756 --> 24:58.061
Where's Aunt Vi?

24:58.105 --> 24:59.628
Oh, she texted me
about a half-hour ago,

24:59.672 --> 25:00.890
said
she was on the way.

25:00.934 --> 25:02.979
Okay.Hopefully, she'll be here soon.

25:03.023 --> 25:04.285
Let me show you around,
alright?

25:04.328 --> 25:06.374
What's up, everybody?
How you doing?

25:06.417 --> 25:08.637
See, this right here, brother,
this is where we keep all

25:08.681 --> 25:10.987
the food and the drinks
stocked up, right here.

25:11.031 --> 25:12.989
You got some beer?Ha ha ha!

25:13.033 --> 25:14.382
I'mma act like
I didn't hear that!

25:14.425 --> 25:15.688
No?

25:15.731 --> 25:18.691
About to get me in trouble
with your auntie.

25:18.734 --> 25:24.131
Oh, so this right here, brother,
this is the War Room.

25:24.174 --> 25:25.698
What happens
in the War Room?

25:25.741 --> 25:27.177
What happens
in the War Room?

25:27.221 --> 25:30.833
Whenever anybody has any issues,
we bring it in here,

25:30.877 --> 25:34.794
discuss it amongst the circle,
man to man, face to face.

25:34.837 --> 25:35.925
I love that.

25:35.969 --> 25:38.145
And this right here,
this is...

25:38.188 --> 25:40.364
I picked this chair
special.

25:40.408 --> 25:42.671
For Prosper,
when he gets better.

25:42.715 --> 25:43.846
Not if, but when.

25:43.890 --> 25:46.109
-When.
-Yeah.

25:46.153 --> 25:48.068
This is what I wanted
to show you.

25:48.111 --> 25:49.286
What you think
about this?

25:49.330 --> 25:50.679
Think you could do something
with it?

25:50.723 --> 25:51.985
Man, this is perfect.

25:52.028 --> 25:53.116
-Mr. Desonier?
-Yes, sir.

25:53.160 --> 25:54.378
-We're ready for you.
-Alright.

25:54.422 --> 25:56.772
Give me one moment, alright?
Whew.

25:56.816 --> 25:57.947
They ready for you.

25:57.991 --> 25:59.775
Show time.

25:59.819 --> 26:01.081
Hang easy, alright?

26:01.124 --> 26:02.386
Yeah.
Thanks, man.

26:02.430 --> 26:03.692
You got this.
I got it?

26:03.736 --> 26:05.825
Yeah.
Okay, let's get it.

26:05.868 --> 26:08.218
♪♪

26:09.655 --> 26:16.531
♪♪

26:16.575 --> 26:23.407
♪♪

26:23.451 --> 26:26.715
Hi.

26:26.759 --> 26:28.848
Thank God you're here.

26:28.891 --> 26:30.589
What's going on,
Celine?

26:36.638 --> 26:40.337
Gabriel, honey,

26:40.381 --> 26:42.601
go put this away
in the bathroom for me.

26:42.644 --> 26:44.298
Go on.

26:46.517 --> 26:48.476
Gabriel got ahold of my phone,

26:48.519 --> 26:49.869
and he texted his dad,
and I --

26:49.912 --> 26:51.087
I don't know.

26:51.131 --> 26:52.654
I don't know how
this thing work,

26:52.698 --> 26:54.700
but he sent him a text message,
and I'm just afraid

26:54.743 --> 26:56.832
that he's gonna be able
to track us down here.

26:56.876 --> 27:01.184
I know he's so mad that I took
Gabriel, that he just might...

27:01.228 --> 27:02.577
He just might find me.

27:02.621 --> 27:04.927
A-And if he find me,
I don't know what he gonna do.

27:04.971 --> 27:07.408
Okay, okay, okay.

27:07.451 --> 27:09.758
We don't know nothing
for sure yet.

27:09.802 --> 27:12.021
So let me just
look at this.

27:14.763 --> 27:18.375
This -- This message
don't look like it, uh...

27:18.419 --> 27:19.942
It looked like
this timed out.

27:19.986 --> 27:23.032
What that mean?

27:23.076 --> 27:25.556
Uh...
Where?

27:25.600 --> 27:29.517
This message was never sent,
baby.

27:29.560 --> 27:34.174
Girl, thank God
for some crappy hotel Wi-Fi.

27:36.480 --> 27:40.136
I d-- I didn't know that.

27:40.180 --> 27:42.051
I just saw the message,
and I just freaked out.

27:42.095 --> 27:43.749
I am so sorry.

27:43.792 --> 27:45.272
I done made you come
all the way over here,

27:45.315 --> 27:46.839
and you done already been
so kind

27:46.882 --> 27:50.233
and put us up in this room,
and I just hate to impose.

27:50.277 --> 27:51.495
No, no, no, no.

27:51.539 --> 27:53.062
Stop.

27:53.106 --> 27:56.283
Baby, this ain't no problem
for me.

27:56.326 --> 27:58.633
I been where you been.

28:02.245 --> 28:03.594
I'm done.

28:03.638 --> 28:05.031
Can we eat?

28:05.074 --> 28:06.597
Mm, just give us a second,
okay?

28:06.641 --> 28:10.297
Um, why don't you go get
the paper plates and the forks.

28:14.170 --> 28:16.695
He is struggling so much
with the idea

28:16.738 --> 28:20.699
that he can't see
or talk to his dad.

28:20.742 --> 28:22.483
Can you...

28:22.526 --> 28:24.920
maybe just talk to him just for
a second, please,

28:24.964 --> 28:28.184
before you go, Vi?

28:28.228 --> 28:30.709
Gabriel, baby,
come on over here.

28:34.277 --> 28:36.410
Oh, thank you, baby.

28:39.065 --> 28:43.809
Now, your mama tells me that you
tried to text your daddy today.

28:43.852 --> 28:45.027
Yeah.

28:45.071 --> 28:47.247
I said,
"Happy birthday."

28:47.290 --> 28:49.728
He didn't write me back,
though.

28:49.771 --> 28:54.689
Do you know why you and your
mama had to leave your daddy?

28:57.213 --> 29:01.000
'Cause Daddy gets
too angry sometimes.

29:01.043 --> 29:03.698
That's right.

29:03.742 --> 29:08.790
So it's real important
that you don't try to call

29:08.834 --> 29:13.316
or text messages to him,
at least for a little while.

29:13.360 --> 29:15.188
Do you understand?

29:15.231 --> 29:16.493
Yes, ma'am.

29:16.537 --> 29:18.278
Okay.

29:19.845 --> 29:22.673
Y'all got all of this good
food here.

29:22.717 --> 29:24.850
I am going to
let you eat it.

29:24.893 --> 29:27.026
Can you stay and have
dinner with us?

29:27.069 --> 29:28.679
Please, Miss Vi?

29:28.723 --> 29:30.769
Nobody else ever comes
to see us.

29:30.812 --> 29:34.120
Baby, I --
I would love to.

29:34.163 --> 29:36.644
But I have somewhere
I need to be.

29:39.081 --> 29:40.779
We got more than enough.

29:48.264 --> 29:49.831
Well,
what y'all got here?

29:49.875 --> 29:51.485
Corn-beef hash.

29:51.528 --> 29:54.444
I think I just might have
a little bit of that.

29:54.488 --> 29:56.446
I'll get another plate.

29:59.101 --> 30:02.322
Baby, it's okay.

30:02.365 --> 30:04.324
Thank you.

30:06.369 --> 30:09.416
I'm just gonna run
to the bathroom, alright?

30:23.517 --> 30:25.649
Hey, it's Hollywood.
Leave a message.

30:25.693 --> 30:27.173
Hey, baby.

30:27.216 --> 30:28.652
Listen, I ran into a bit

30:28.696 --> 30:31.003
of a plumbing problem
here at the diner.

30:31.046 --> 30:32.656
Nothing major.

30:32.700 --> 30:35.877
So, um, I'm gonna do that,
and then I'll be right there.

30:35.921 --> 30:38.227
♪♪

30:41.796 --> 30:43.842
If it ain't
the queen herself.

30:43.885 --> 30:45.321
Darla: Hey.

30:45.365 --> 30:46.627
What's all this, baby?

30:46.670 --> 30:49.848
All of this is
my healthy pregnancy meal.

30:49.891 --> 30:51.327
Oh.

30:51.371 --> 30:54.853
So, we have a kale salad
with dried apricot and almonds.

30:54.896 --> 30:56.376
Okay.

30:56.419 --> 31:00.336
We have quinoa with avocado
and roasted beetroot.

31:00.380 --> 31:04.558
So, uh...
where's all the meat?

31:04.601 --> 31:08.127
Ha! I am limiting the meat
to only three times per week.

31:08.170 --> 31:09.955
Three times?

31:09.998 --> 31:11.260
Oh, okay.

31:11.304 --> 31:12.914
Gonna be ordering
a whole lot of pizza

31:12.958 --> 31:14.568
during this pregnancy, huh?No, we're not.

31:14.611 --> 31:17.397
You're doing this all
with me.

31:17.440 --> 31:18.964
Every step of the way.

31:19.007 --> 31:21.880
Yeah, you right.

31:21.923 --> 31:23.185
Oh, um...

31:23.229 --> 31:24.839
do you mind
picking up my pills?

31:24.883 --> 31:26.797
The pharmacy closes
at 7:00,

31:26.841 --> 31:29.757
and I'm in the middle
of all this.

31:31.977 --> 31:33.543
Yeah, uh...

31:33.587 --> 31:35.589
I guess I --
I got you.

31:39.941 --> 31:41.682
You okay?

31:44.772 --> 31:47.862
You know how sometimes
it feel like...

31:47.906 --> 31:50.691
the Saints gonna win
if you don't watch the game?

31:50.734 --> 31:52.519
Mm-hmm.

31:52.562 --> 31:55.696
That's kind of
how I feel.

31:55.739 --> 31:58.829
Just being
at the hospital...

31:58.873 --> 32:00.179
made me feel
some type of way.

32:00.222 --> 32:01.354
Mm.

32:01.397 --> 32:02.746
Don't think like that.

32:02.790 --> 32:03.573
I know.

32:03.617 --> 32:06.315
Prosper's strong.

32:06.359 --> 32:08.709
You right.

32:08.752 --> 32:10.972
Don't worry about the pills.
I can get them tomorrow.

32:11.016 --> 32:12.060
Nah.

32:12.104 --> 32:13.757
No, honestly --
I got it.

32:13.801 --> 32:16.717
Okay.

32:16.760 --> 32:18.937
About to
go handle that.

32:18.980 --> 32:22.418
Okay.

32:22.462 --> 32:24.464
Quinoa on your lips.

32:26.292 --> 32:28.468
I'll see you later.See ya later.

32:29.948 --> 32:31.079
[ Woman on telephone
shouting indistinctly ]

32:31.123 --> 32:33.125
Yes, Ms. DuChamps.

32:33.168 --> 32:35.040
Mm-hmm.

32:35.083 --> 32:38.304
I can assure you we will have
in place measures

32:38.347 --> 32:40.349
to make sure
that any future event --

32:40.393 --> 32:42.612
[ Line beeps]

32:42.656 --> 32:48.488
♪ Sometimes I decide
where I should be ♪

32:48.531 --> 32:54.233
♪ Sometimes life
just happens to me ♪

32:54.276 --> 33:01.153
♪♪

33:01.196 --> 33:07.942
♪♪

33:07.986 --> 33:09.988
Nova: I figure since you weren't
answering my calls,

33:10.031 --> 33:11.685
better come see you
in person.

33:11.728 --> 33:13.730
Nova, I have a lot on my plate
right now with Daddy,

33:13.774 --> 33:16.516
and I really don't have --This won't take long.

33:19.780 --> 33:21.825
Um...
sorry about the mess.

33:21.869 --> 33:24.872
I -- I didn't have time
to unpack.

33:29.703 --> 33:32.836
Read your book.

33:32.880 --> 33:38.059
I saw you on that panel with
Patrisse Cullors on YouTube.

33:38.103 --> 33:41.062
Wow.

33:41.106 --> 33:43.369
Look at us.

33:43.412 --> 33:44.979
You remember
senior year?

33:45.023 --> 33:46.024
Mm.

33:46.067 --> 33:47.677
Waged that campaign
at school

33:47.721 --> 33:49.897
to make them accommodate
your veganism.

33:49.940 --> 33:51.551
A noble cause.

33:51.594 --> 33:54.684
Doomed but noble.

33:54.728 --> 33:56.121
You were always meant
to be an activist.

33:56.164 --> 33:59.037
Just surprised
you stayed in Louisiana.

33:59.080 --> 34:00.734
My family is here.

34:00.777 --> 34:02.692
Family means a lot
to me.

34:02.736 --> 34:05.304
It means a lot to me,
too.

34:05.347 --> 34:08.437
I know it does.

34:08.481 --> 34:11.005
Prosper is family
to me.

34:11.049 --> 34:13.529
And to Aunt Vi.
Don't shut her out.

34:13.573 --> 34:16.097
Your aunt
was disrespectful.

34:16.141 --> 34:18.273
And she needs to learn
to respect me.

34:18.317 --> 34:20.362
You've known Aunt Vi
since we were kids, Billie.

34:20.406 --> 34:22.538
You know she only wants
what's best for everyone,

34:22.582 --> 34:23.713
especially Prosper.

34:23.757 --> 34:26.716
No, she thinks she knows
what's best.

34:26.760 --> 34:28.892
Telling me what to do
like I'm a child.

34:28.936 --> 34:31.286
She was always like that,
in everybody's business.

34:31.330 --> 34:34.985
Not everything around here
revolves around the Bordelons.

34:35.029 --> 34:37.031
Whatever my aunt may have
said or done,

34:37.075 --> 34:40.121
it came from
a place of love.

34:40.165 --> 34:43.733
She brought your father
into her home during COVID.

34:46.127 --> 34:48.564
I offered Daddy to come stay
with me and the kids,

34:48.608 --> 34:51.872
and he turned me down.

34:51.915 --> 34:56.616
Rather be at Vi's than
spend time with his own blood.

34:56.659 --> 35:00.141
You've been gone a long time,
Billie.

35:00.185 --> 35:03.275
Prosper loves St. Jo.

35:03.318 --> 35:05.581
And he didn't
want to leave,

35:05.625 --> 35:09.585
and he didn't want you
to worry about him.

35:09.629 --> 35:13.676
Look, we may not be
Prosper's blood...

35:13.720 --> 35:16.636
but we are family.

35:16.679 --> 35:20.074
Vi should be
in that room.

35:20.118 --> 35:21.815
She's earned that.

35:24.731 --> 35:26.646
And you owe me.

35:31.520 --> 35:33.392
Okay.

35:33.435 --> 35:35.872
I'll call the hospital.

35:35.916 --> 35:37.613
But please keep your aunt
in check.

35:37.657 --> 35:41.095
Thank you.

35:41.139 --> 35:43.184
I'll let Aunt Vi
and the others know.

35:45.969 --> 35:49.451
[ Door opens, closes ]

35:49.495 --> 35:51.323
Reporter: We will then see highs
in the mid 80s...

35:51.366 --> 35:53.194
Oh, hey, Vi.
Where you been?

35:53.238 --> 35:55.153
Drove by the diner,
it was all dark.

35:55.196 --> 35:56.197
Baby, I'm so sorry.

35:56.241 --> 35:57.807
By the time I got to
The Real Spot,

35:57.851 --> 35:58.982
they said
you had just left.

35:59.026 --> 36:00.636
We must have
crossed each other.

36:00.680 --> 36:02.595
Mm-hmm.

36:04.379 --> 36:05.337
How'd everything go?

36:05.380 --> 36:06.642
It was perfect.

36:06.686 --> 36:09.993
You know,
except you wasn't there.

36:10.037 --> 36:13.214
Come on and sit down.
They about to show my segment.

36:13.258 --> 36:15.695
Reporter #2: In our next
"Comeback after COVID" exposé,

36:15.738 --> 36:17.697
we highlight Hollywood Desonier

36:17.740 --> 36:20.178
on his quest to open
The Real Spot.

36:20.221 --> 36:21.918
Reporter #3: Mr. Desonier,
what was your objective

36:21.962 --> 36:23.355
behind The Real Spot?

36:23.398 --> 36:24.878
You know, it's funny
you ask me that.

36:24.921 --> 36:27.054
People always do.
They say...

36:27.097 --> 36:29.926
Oh, my God.
Look how handsome you are.

36:29.970 --> 36:32.755
Yeah, I do look good,
don't I?

36:32.799 --> 36:34.844
Guess I didn't need
my good-luck charm after all.

36:34.888 --> 36:36.455
But more than that, you know,
it's a thing of

36:36.498 --> 36:38.108
brothers getting together,
supporting each other.

36:38.152 --> 36:39.327
[ Knock on door ]

36:43.810 --> 36:46.029
Hey.
Loretta made you an extra plate.

36:46.073 --> 36:48.423
She said to say thank you
for the pie you left

36:48.467 --> 36:49.685
when I first moved in.

36:49.729 --> 36:51.296
And then she apologized
for eating it

36:51.339 --> 36:52.297
before I got back home.

36:52.340 --> 36:53.776
Oh, I don't blame her.

36:53.820 --> 36:55.778
My Aunt Violet's pies
are pretty irresistible.

36:55.822 --> 36:57.867
Apparently so.

36:57.911 --> 36:59.608
Yeah, she's never been one
for restraint.

36:59.652 --> 37:01.175
Since we were kids.

37:01.219 --> 37:02.089
Oh, wow.

37:02.132 --> 37:04.091
Y'all
childhood sweethearts?

37:04.134 --> 37:06.267
I'm sorry, she --
she's my sister.

37:08.530 --> 37:10.184
Oh.

37:10.228 --> 37:12.447
Oh, my goodness.
[ Chuckles ]

37:12.491 --> 37:14.057
Wow.
Um, I'm sorry.

37:14.101 --> 37:15.581
I-I assumed.

37:15.624 --> 37:18.584
And can't go making assumptions.No, it's not a problem.

37:18.627 --> 37:20.020
She was just helping me
get situated

37:20.063 --> 37:21.587
'cause I had to move while
I was traveling,

37:21.630 --> 37:24.111
yada yada.
I see.

37:24.154 --> 37:27.723
Nothing excuses
the pie theft.

37:27.767 --> 37:29.551
Here you go.

37:29.595 --> 37:33.294
She does make a mean
vegetable casserole.

37:33.338 --> 37:35.905
This is truly...

37:35.949 --> 37:38.517
I don't know.
And I...

37:38.560 --> 37:40.867
I needed
some kindness today.

37:40.910 --> 37:43.913
It's been a long day.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.872
Need to talk about it?

37:45.915 --> 37:47.787
I got good ears.

37:52.444 --> 37:55.273
This hashtag...

37:55.316 --> 37:58.319
was trending for hours
yesterday.

37:58.363 --> 38:00.147
"Cancel Nova Bordelon."

38:00.190 --> 38:01.931
It's because I haven't
publicly addressed

38:01.975 --> 38:03.324
a relationship that I had

38:03.368 --> 38:06.632
that people feel stands
in contrast to my values.

38:06.675 --> 38:08.764
How do you feel
about that?

38:08.808 --> 38:11.332
I express myself
in my work.

38:11.376 --> 38:12.942
I don't owe anyone
an explanation

38:12.986 --> 38:14.292
about my personal life.

38:14.335 --> 38:15.597
100%.

38:15.641 --> 38:18.948
But when you're asking people
to follow you,

38:18.992 --> 38:21.299
high expectations
come with the territory.

38:23.475 --> 38:26.913
You have a gift.

38:26.956 --> 38:29.959
Comes at a cost,
maybe.

38:30.003 --> 38:32.658
Yeah, I don't know.

38:32.701 --> 38:34.399
Mm, maybe.

38:36.923 --> 38:38.011
My mother
wrote in her journals

38:38.054 --> 38:39.621
that her connections
to her gifts

38:39.665 --> 38:45.453
were always strongest when
she was living in her truth.

38:45.497 --> 38:48.456
I'm living in my truth.

38:48.500 --> 38:51.459
I lost a man I loved
so I can live in my truth.

38:54.332 --> 38:58.423
Just don't understand
why everything seems so off.

38:59.902 --> 39:02.992
I'm sorry.

39:03.036 --> 39:04.864
I was at the hospital
with a family member all night

39:04.907 --> 39:07.214
after an event I planned
went off the rails,

39:07.257 --> 39:09.259
and then this,
and just, uh...

39:11.653 --> 39:14.395
I just need to go to bed.

39:14.439 --> 39:16.441
I think.

39:16.484 --> 39:18.356
I hear you.

39:18.399 --> 39:20.749
Sleep is a good fix.

39:20.793 --> 39:23.491
Food is, too.

39:23.535 --> 39:26.538
Take a little time
to take care of yourself.

39:26.581 --> 39:29.889
We need your voice.

39:29.932 --> 39:32.631
To brighter days.

39:32.674 --> 39:34.372
To brighter days.

